Html tag:
    A tag is a keyword enclosed in < > used to define content.

    E.g:

    <h1></h1>
    <p></p>
    <img>
    <a></a>

    most tags have opening and closing <p> </p>...
    some tags are selfclosing/ empty <img> , <br>...

Html element:
    html elements include opening tag + content + closing tag.

    <p> --> opening tag
    this is an content --> content
    </p> --> closing tag
    Full line = html element

    E.g:

    <h1>website</h1>

    <a href="#">click</a>

Html attribute:
    Attributes give a extra information to a tags.
    They are written inside the opening tag in key="value" format.

    E.g:
    -
     _____________________________________________
    | Attribute | Used in Tag | Purpose           |
    | --------- | ----------- | ----------------- |
    | `href`    | `<a>`       | Link URL          |
    | `src`     | `<img>`     | Image path        |
    | `alt`     | `<img>`     | Alternative text  |
    | `id`      | any tag     | Unique identifier |
    | `class`   | any tag     | Group styling     |
    | `style`   | any tag     | Inline CSS        |

